81	/// `id` has gone away, so its registry entry and locks clear immediately.
82	///
83	/// Used by the sidebar plugin's pane-death hook: when a cockpit-spawned agent
84	/// pane closes, the plugin runs this command to call the daemon's
85	/// `agent_leave` MCP tool on behalf of the dead pane. Without it, a closed
86	/// cockpit-spawned agent (which uses a stable `?agent=<id>` key) would
87	/// linger in the registry indefinitely because declared identities never
88	/// idle-prune.
